
[1]slowly

   SLOWLY, adv.

   1. With moderate motion; not rapidly; not with velocity or celerity;
   as, to walk slowly.

   2. Not soon; not early; not in a little time; not with hasty advance;
   as a country that rises slowly into importance.

   3. Not hastily; not rashly; not with precipitation; as, he determines
   slowly.

   4. Not promptly; not readily; as, he learns slowly.

   5. Tardily; with slow progress. The building proceeds slowly.
